		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I did it here for a long time, too.  It was getting absolutely insane (and our memberlist is still padded out by 1000+ I'm sure).  But 99.99% of the accounts I was deleting back then were inactive anyways, and couldn't post.  They were registering like 10 accounts per day.
<br />
<br />Then I patched in a simple security question that someone had suggested, that cut off the flow of spammers for a while, but obviously the asshole spambots are getting smarter now.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" />
<br />
<br />If they can get past a simple (but customized) question, it's hard telling what other measures they can bypass also..

		

		</td>
	</tr>
